    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-06-11T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-06-11T18:00:00-05:00" n="503"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d503">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.252/5–1947: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in Chile</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-06-11T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 11, 1947—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>283. Dept surprised coolness Bernstein, Vergara and statement treaty ultimately
                    dependent results Geneva conference ref Embdes 15297 May 19, 1947.<note n="82"
                        xml:id="d503fn1">Not printed.</note> Under circumstances considered
                    desirable now above all secure reaffirmation Chilean interest in treaty.</p>
                <p>Unless strongly felt attitude Vergara, Bernstein accurately and fully reflects
                    views <gloss target="#t_FonMin1">FonMin</gloss> or other serious objection
                    perceived, <gloss target="#t_Emb1">Emb</gloss> instructed approach <gloss
                        target="#t_FonMin1">FonMin</gloss> with view securing reaffirmation even in
                    general terms pointing out not immediately seeking opening formal
                    negotiations.</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_urinfo1">Urinfo</gloss> only Dept feels present inopportune
                    press further for Chilean views specific articles US draft or attempt conduct
                    concrete discussion.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
